<t>CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, date_of_birth DATE)

CREATE TABLE accounts (account_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT REFERENCES users(id), account_type STRING, balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE transactions (transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT REFERENCES accounts(account_id), transaction_type STRING, amount DECIMAL(10, 2), transaction_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE categories (category_id INT PRIMARY KEY, category_name STRING, parent_category_id INT REFERENCES categories(category_id))</t><s>SELECT * FROM users</s>

CREATE TABLE categories (category_id INT PRIMARY KEY, category_name STRING, parent_category_id INT REFERENCES categories(category_id))

CREATE TABLE accounts (account_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT REFERENCES users(id), account_type STRING, balance DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>select account_id, transaction_type, amount from transactions</s>

CREATE TABLE categories (category_id INT PRIMARY KEY, category_name STRING, parent_category_id INT REFERENCES categories(category_id))</t><s>SELECT * FROM users JOIN accounts ON users.id = accounts.user_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, date_of_birth DATE)

CREATE TABLE accounts (account_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT REFERENCES users(id), account_type STRING, balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE transactions (transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT REFERENCES accounts(account_id), transaction_type STRING, amount DECIMAL(10, 2), transaction_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE categories (category_id INT PRIMARY KEY, category_name STRING, parent_category_id INT REFERENCES categories(category_id))</t><s>select * from users join accounts on users.id = accounts.user_id</s>

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE budget (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, category_id INT, amount DECIMAL(10, 2), month INT, year INT)</t><s>SELECT * FROM users</s>

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)</t><s>select * from accounts</s>

CREATE TABLE categories (id INT PRIMARY KEY, category_name VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)</t><s>SELECT account_name, balance FROM accounts</s>

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE categories (id INT PRIMARY KEY, category_name VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE budget (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, category_id INT, amount DECIMAL(10, 2), month INT, year INT)</t><s>SELECT account_id, transaction_type, amount FROM transactions WHERE id = 1</s>

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>SELECT account_id, transaction_type, amount FROM transactions WHERE id = 1</s>

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE budget (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, category_id INT, amount DECIMAL(10, 2), month INT, year INT)

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)</t><s>SELECT * FROM budget</s>

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)</t><s>select * from users join accounts on users.id = accounts.user_id</s>

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))</t><s>select * from users join accounts on users.id = accounts.user_id</s>

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50))</t><s>SELECT * FROM accounts WHERE balance > 1000</s>

CREATE TABLE budget (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, category_id INT, amount DECIMAL(10, 2), month INT, year INT)

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50))</t><s>select * from users order by name desc</s>

CREATE TABLE accounts (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, account_name VARCHAR(50), balance DECIMAL(10, 2))

CREATE TABLE users (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)</t><s>SELECT AVG(amount) FROM transactions</s>

CREATE TABLE transactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY, account_id INT, transaction_type VARCHAR(10), amount DECIMAL(10, 2), date TIMESTAMP)</t><s>SELECT AVG(amount) FROM transactions</s>
